        "details": {
            "description": "<p>The equilibrium of the brown mold and lava river is disturbed, creating bubbles of molten stone that burst and spew burning debris.</p>",
            "disable": "<p>@Check[type:nature|dc:14|name:Clear mold|traits:uncommon,complex,environmental,fire] or @Check[type:survival|dc:14|name:Clear mold|traits:uncommon,complex,environmental,fire] or @Check[type:thievery|dc:17|name:Clear mold|traits:uncommon,complex,environmental,fire] to clear your square and all adjacent squares of the mold; the churning lava does not target creatures in cleared squares with its spatter attack, but the hazard is not destroyed until every square has been cleared of mold.</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 1
            },
            "reset": "<p>If not completely destroyed, the mold spreads to one additional square within 10 feet of lava each day until it fully regenerates and regains its state of equilibrium. If every square is cleaned of mold, the hazard is destroyed.</p>",
            "routine": "<p><span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> On the its initiative, the churning lava targets a random creature in the area with a ranged spatter attack as a magma bubble bursts.</p>"
